snippet.textDisplay: The reason why Hillary Rodham Clinton can now relax is because the chicanery of the GOP has been completely revealed. I always voted for Hillary Clinton but even I recognise that if she'd won the Presidency, the GOP would've just carried on as they had for over 25 years in terms of demonising this incredibly capable and accomplished woman - whom, gender aside, was one of the most qualified candidates for the Presidency EVER. She would've persevered and likely been a great President but the GOP would've maintained their playbook for many elections to come. Now, with Trump, we've seen how morally and ethically bankrupt they are; the reckoning is here, it's happening now, and as a political party, they will be in the wilderness for a long time to come, if they survive at all. Hillary Clinton was always between a rock and hard place as an intelligent woman with political power, as she described in Part 2. What we have instead of her presidency, is a sea change in American politics, which will decimate this so-called "conservative" party. Trump gave us the #metoo movement and inadvertently empowered women. It's all painful but there's a lot to be grateful for. Hillary Clinton did not lose in vain - the change did come.
